@node part1 "What is it?"

            EasyInterest is a compound interest calculator.

            It can take an initial balance (say Ł1000 UK pounds),
            a rate of interest (say 15%) and a time period over
            which to calculate (say 20 years).

            The program also offers you intermediate balance reports,
            for more information see the 'usage' section linked below.

            It then progressively muliplies the balance at the
            specified rate of interest over the time period to
            calculate what the final balance would be.

            Most people might do this on a calculator, but for
            time periods of more than a few years it gets
            increasingly complicated and easy to make mistakes.

            EasyInterest simplifies all of this.



            To discover why I created EasyInterest click @{"here" link part6}.

            If you want to run it you'll want to know the @{"system requirements" link part2}.

            As the program is not yet perfect, please read the @{"bugs" link part5} section.

            Or jump straight to @{"usage" link part4} for instructions on
            how to access the program.


                        @{"Return to contents" link main}
@endnode

@node part2 "System Requirements"

            @{b}@{u}Minimum system required (this is untested):@{uu}@{ub}

            An Amiga, 90Kb RAM, Workbench 3.0+, MUI 3.8

            @{b}@{u}Recommended system:@{uu}@{ub}

            Amiga1200, 150Kb RAM free, Workbench 3.9, MUI 3.8


            @{b}@{u}Development system:@{uu}@{ub}

            @{b}Hardware@{ub}
            Amiga1200PPC in Power Tower, Blizzard 603e+(210)/'060(50) with 80Mb RAM,
            BlizzardVision Graphics Card, 6.4Gb hard disk, Philips 109S10 19" monitor,
            2Gb JAZ2 drive, Pace 'Solo' 56K Modem.

            @{b}Software@{ub}
            Workbench 3.9, Golded 6 and StormC4.0


                        @{"Return to contents" link main}
@endnode

